> Now I have no glue how to trace the problem further down, but I would
> love to keep
> the outstanding ISDN performance of 2.2.14.
I don't know what the problem could be, but as a workaround you could try
enabling ide-scsi emulation and using scsi drivers. Maybe it helps, maybe
not -- but it might be worth a try.
ide-scsi is meant mainly for cd-r burners but I suppose it works fine with
ordinary cdrom drives too.
